&lt;h3&gt;Satellite Dreams&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="blog-meta"&gt;Written during a late night analyzing irrigation patterns ‚Ä¢ 2024&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;
From space, the Earth is a canvas&lt;br&gt;
of green and brown and blue&lt;br&gt;
I trace the lines of human need&lt;br&gt;
across the satellite view&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

Each pixel tells a story&lt;br&gt;
of water, soil, and sun&lt;br&gt;
of farmers and their families&lt;br&gt;
of work that's never done&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

I teach the computer to see&lt;br&gt;
what we've been ignoring&lt;br&gt;
turning terabytes into hope&lt;br&gt;
and data into caring
&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Kelp Dog Ode&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="blog-meta"&gt;Inspired by my dog's seaweed obsession ‚Ä¢ 2024&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;
My dog thinks kelp is the world's best snack&lt;br&gt;
she'll eat it fresh or dried&lt;br&gt;
from the beach or from the water&lt;br&gt;
with uncontainable pride&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

I tell her it's not normal&lt;br&gt;
but she doesn't seem to care&lt;br&gt;
she's found her perfect food&lt;br&gt;
and it's everywhere&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

Maybe she knows something&lt;br&gt;
about the ocean's gifts&lt;br&gt;
that we humans are still learning&lt;br&gt;
as our understanding shifts
&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;Data Becomes Action&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="blog-meta"&gt;After organizing my first big beach cleanup ‚Ä¢ 2023&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;
We started with numbers&lt;br&gt;
plastic pieces counted&lt;br&gt;
beach surveys conducted&lt;br&gt;
data points mounted&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

But numbers don't clean beaches&lt;br&gt;
or change human hearts&lt;br&gt;
so we put down our spreadsheets&lt;br&gt;
and picked up our parts&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

Fifty people showed up&lt;br&gt;
with gloves and with hope&lt;br&gt;
proving that data becomes action&lt;br&gt;
when we stop being spectators&lt;br&gt;
and start being scope
